{"pageProps":{"articles":[{"title":"My search for a functional web framework","id":"my-search-for-a-functional-web-framework","file":"<p class=\"c3\"><span class=\"c2\"></span></p><p class=\"c8 title\" id=\"h.oeeynhvojrte\"><span class=\"c6\">Introduction</span></p><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">Haskell may be my favorite programming language, but I do most of my programming on the web,where I am forced to use javascript. While I also love javascript, I do wish I could use haskell or some other functional language on the frontend. My dream is to have something like next.js, but written in a functional language. I really like next.js, especially the static building. </span></p><h1 class=\"c1\" id=\"h.lidx6ynyll3f\"><span class=\"c5\">Features I want</span></h1><ul class=\"c9 lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-0 start\"><li class=\"c4 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c2\">server-side rendering</span></li><li class=\"c4 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c2\">functional languages</span></li><li class=\"c4 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c2\">static site generation</span></li><li class=\"c4 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c2\">single page applications</span></li><li class=\"c4 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c2\">minimal boilerplate</span></li></ul><p class=\"c3\"><span class=\"c2\"></span></p><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">There are several things I have tried, but I haven&#39;t like any of them.</span></p><p class=\"c3\"><span class=\"c2\"></span></p><p class=\"c8 title\" id=\"h.9l1yihmvjoa6\"><span class=\"c6\">Elm</span></p><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">I tried elm once, but the routing didn&#39;t work also it doesn&#39;t have ssr, ssg, or spa. In fact, the first example for an elm spa has mountains of boilerplate, so I don&#39;t like it</span></p><p class=\"c8 title\" id=\"h.rrciwg1fkme0\"><span class=\"c6\">Purescript</span></p><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">Purescript might be good, but there is not much tooling, and routing is bad.</span></p><h1 class=\"c1\" id=\"h.64zlts26y24m\"><span class=\"c5\">Hakyll</span></h1><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">This has static site generation and it is in haskell, but it doesn&#39;t have SSR</span></p><h1 class=\"c1\" id=\"h.z9vcx99wc8pi\"><span class=\"c5\">Conclusion</span></h1><p class=\"c4\"><span class=\"c2\">I think for the foreseeable future I will continue to use Next.js. I may prefer functional programming to javascript, but next.js is so good to use for SSR and SSG that I truly have no other options for a web framework. </span></p><p class=\"c3\"><span class=\"c2\"></span></p><p class=\"c3\"><span class=\"c2\"></span></p>","style":"ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-8{list-style-type:none}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-0>li:before{content:\"\\0025cf  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-1>li:before{content:\"\\0025cb  \"}li.li-bullet-0:before{margin-left:-18pt;white-space:nowrap;display:inline-block;min-width:18pt}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-6>li:before{content:\"\\0025cf  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-5>li:before{content:\"\\0025a0  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-7>li:before{content:\"\\0025cb  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-4>li:before{content:\"\\0025cb  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-8>li:before{content:\"\\0025a0  \"}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-4{list-style-type:none}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-2>li:before{content:\"\\0025a0  \"}.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-3>li:before{content:\"\\0025cf  \"}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-5{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-6{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-7{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-0{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-1{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-2{list-style-type:none}ul.lst-kix_esuwha2p9tza-3{list-style-type:none}ol{margin:0;padding:0}table td,table th{padding:0}.c5{color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:20pt;font-family:\"Arial\";font-style:normal}.c2{color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:11pt;font-family:\"Arial\";font-style:normal}.c8{padding-top:0pt;paddi